TrafficHelper uses OpenAPI as an interface between the frontend and backend
The contract specifications are at /Contracts
42crunch's OpenAPI (swagger) editor visualizes the potential YAML file [11]
Jim Schubert's openapi-generator extension is then applied to generate implementations for the YAML [12, 17]
Consists of implementation of
    routes_impl: Returns a series of coordinates and data to plot from the API
    preferences_impl: Accepts the user's preferences and sets the preferences and returns them through the API
    points_impl: Accepts and sets the user's start and end points in either coordinate or address form


